Add More Data in a Recipe
You can add columns of data from related objects to existing data in a recipe. Depending on how you want to combine the new data, use one of the following methods: lookup, left join, right join, inner join, or full outer join.

Available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience.
Available with CRM Analytics, which is available for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions. Also available in Developer Edition.

When you add data to a recipe, select the dataset or connected object that contains the fields that you want to add. Select the key fields to match the records between the existing and new data streams.
Letâ€™s look at an example: adding User fields to Opportunity records using the User ID field from the User object and Opportunity Owner ID field from the Opportunity object as keys.

On the recipe page, click Add Data. Select either Datasets or Connected Data, and choose the dataset or object that you want to add. Choose the join type, select the keys from the left and right data streams, and include additional columns in the Columns to Include section.
Each time you add data, a new step is created in your recipe.
